      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>LEAD: Every time you flip on a light or an appliance, you're buying electricity. Each customer's use varies, of course, but on May 1, the average monthly bill for a Long Island Lighting Company residential customer was $83 for 600 kilowatt hours of electricity. Lilco's and Con Edison's rates are among the highest in the country, so the averages for other areas would have been lower.</p>
      </block>
